<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FDA719637DE02D3E" bold="true" box="[557,641,1572,1593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2154B71FFAD2819FDA719637DE02D3E" box="[557,641,1572,1593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(A) hypopygium, left lateral view; (B) hypopygium, right lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) surstylus, lateral view; (E) hypopygium, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3487993FFAD2819FF4D19C77C982D9E" box="[199,1017,1664,1689]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED2A18FFAD2819FF4D19C77C982D9E" blockId="10.[151,1436,1664,1833]" box="[199,1017,1664,1689]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FF4D19C77E272D9E" bold="true" box="[199,326,1664,1689]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named for the claw-like setae on the hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3487993FFAD2818FF4D19E37AFD2A02" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED2A18FFAD2819FF4D19E37D292C2E" blockId="10.[151,1436,1664,1833]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FF4D19E37E552DBA" bold="true" box="[199,308,1700,1725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">Remarks</emphasis>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC357E9FFAD2819FE6E19E37DDF2DBA" author="Stackelberg" box="[484,702,1700,1725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" refString="Stackelberg, A. A. (1934) Dolichopodidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region, 82, 129 - 176." type="journal article" year="1934">Stackelberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species is included in the third group of 
<taxonomicName id="4C52519BFFAD2819FA8319E27AFD2DBB" box="[1289,1436,1701,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FA8319E27AFD2DBB" box="[1289,1436,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">Hercostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(femora yellow, postocular setae black). In the key to Palaearctic species (Selivanova 
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FBD6198E7BEC2DE7" box="[1116,1165,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2012), the new species runs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C52519BFFAD2819FF7E19AA7DCD2C02" authority="Yang, 1996" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1996" box="[244,684,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beijingensis">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FF7E19AA7D782C03" box="[244,537,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">Hercostomus beijingensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC357E9FFAD2819FDAE19AA7DCD2C02" author="Yang" box="[548,684,1772,1797]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" refString="Yang, D. (1996) New species of Hercostomus and Ludovicius from north China (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 43 (2), 235 - 244. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 19960430207" type="journal article" year="1996">Yang, 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the morphology of hypopygium and following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED2A18FFAD2819FF1D181F7AFD2C8C" blockId="10.[151,1436,1880,1931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">
- Postpedicel with sharp apex. Cercus oval, sharply curved at base, oval at apex............ 
<taxonomicName id="4C52519BFFAD2819FBE4181F7AF82C6A" authority="Yang" authorityName="Yang" box="[1134,1433,1880,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beijingensis">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FBE4181F7A042C6A" box="[1134,1381,1880,1901]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">Hercostomus beijingensis</emphasis>
Yang
</taxonomicName>
- Postpedicel with blunt apex. Cercus narrow long, straight, not curved at base........... 
<taxonomicName id="4C52519BFFAD2819FBDE18327A282C8D" box="[1108,1353,1909,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinitibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FBDE18327A282C8D" box="[1108,1353,1909,1930]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">Hercostomus spinitibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FAC518327AFD2C8C" bold="true" box="[1359,1436,1909,1931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2154B71FFAD2819FAC518327AFD2C8C" box="[1359,1436,1909,1931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED2A18FFAD2819FF4D18FF7B5B2CF3" blockId="10.[151,1433,1974,2036]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">
In the key to Chinese species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC357E9FFAD2819FD9118F07DB92CC8" author="Yang" box="[539,728,1975,1999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" refString="Yang, D., Zhang, L., Wang, M. &amp; Zhu, Y. (2011) Dolichopodidae. Fauna Sinica. Insecta 53. Beijing. Science Press, 1912 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Yang 
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FDD418FF7DEE2CC8" box="[606,655,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
), the new species runs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C52519BFFAD2819FC7C18FF7E562CF4" authority="Yang &amp; Saigusa, 2001" authorityName="Yang &amp; Saigusa" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaolongmensis">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAD2819FC7C18FF7A5F2CC8" box="[1014,1342,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="75">Hercostomus xiaolongmensis</emphasis>
Yang &amp; Saigusa, 2001
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by the following characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED2A18FFAC2818FF1D1FD07AFD2A02" blockId="11.[151,1436,151,261]" pageId="11" pageNumber="76">
- Antennae black. Postpedicel approximately as long as wide. Base of abdomen yellow. Pleura brown-yellow. Cercus curved................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C52519BFFAC2818FC561FF27AF42BCD" authority="Yang &amp; Saigusa" authorityName="Yang &amp; Saigusa" box="[988,1429,181,202]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaolongmensis">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAC2818FC561FF27B942BCD" box="[988,1269,181,202]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="76">Hercostomus xiaolongmensis</emphasis>
Yang &amp; Saigusa
</taxonomicName>
- Antennae mostly yellow. Postpedicel longer than wide. Base of abdomen and pleura green. Cercus straight......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C52519BFFAC2818FBDB1FA87A292A03" box="[1105,1352,239,260]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinitibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAC2818FBDB1FA87A292A03" box="[1105,1352,239,260]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="76">Hercostomus spinitibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B926F60AFFAC2818FAC51FA87AFD2A02" bold="true" box="[1359,1436,239,261]" pageId="11" pageNumber="76">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2154B71FFAC2818FAC51FA87AFD2A02" box="[1359,1436,239,261]" pageId="11" pageNumber="76" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
